=========================================================== 1 ==================
UML DIAGRAMS WITH DOXYGEN
=========================================================== 1 ==================
[KF, 10.10.2014]
UML-like class diagrams can be obtained automatically using doxygen:

* Set the following tags in doc/Doxyfile.in:

    EXTRACT_ALL            = YES
    HAVE_DOT               = YES
    UML_LOOK               = YES

Source:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4755913/how-to-use-doxygen-to-create-uml-class-diagrams-from-c-source
Last accessed: 10.10.2014.

* Private (static) variables and methods will be shown using:

    EXTRACT_PRIVATE        = YES
    EXTRACT_PACKAGE        = YES
    EXTRACT_STATIC         = YES

* Shows template relations and set the number of fields within classes to a
  given value:

    UML_LIMIT_NUM_FIELDS   = 10
    TEMPLATE_RELATIONS     = YES


=========================================================== 4 ==================
DEVELOPERS ONLY: INSTALLING GoogleTest FROM SOURCES
=========================================================== 4 ==================
* Download the source files from

     http://code.google.com/p/googlemock

* Extract the zip-file via unzip, then go to the directory of
  gtest-1.6.0 and run the configure script:

    unzip gtest-1.6.0.zip
    cd gtest-1.6.0
    ./configure --prefix=/opt/gtest-1.6.0

* This means that the library (including GoogleMock) will be installed
  in /opt/gtest-1.6.0/lib. Then, compile the sources via make.

    make;

* Now, install the libraries using make. Call "make -i install" as root (su...).
  The option "-i" is important! Still as root, create a symbolic link:

    su
    make -i install
    ln -sf /opt/gtest-1.6.0 /opt/gtest

* Finally, add the library directory to the the LD_LIBRARY_PATH. Therefore,
  open ~/.bashrc and the following line to the file:

    export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/opt/gtest

* Start a new console in order to activate the new LD_LIBRARY_PATH.
  Now, GoogleTest and GoogleMock should be properly installed!


=========================================================== 6 ==================
SCAFES AND SVN -- A SMALL HOWTO
=========================================================== 6 ==================
# SVN general
# -----------
# All SVN commands should be executed in the root folder of the software
#   (normally: trunk).
# On system with a module system, it is necessary sometimes that SVN is loaded
# as a module (ZIH cluster Atlas, e.g.).
#   module load svn
#   export SVN_EDITOR=vim

# SVN check in
# ------------
# Before local modified data are checked in, one has to update to the newest
# revision and see the changes to this new revision (in order to remember
# the changes one has made).
#     svn update
#     svn diff
#     svn ci
# If "svn ci" is called without the option "-m" the correspding editor
# will open automatically (normally vim) and will show a list of all
# files modified (or added, deleted etc.).
# Please delete the first 3 lines of the file and comment the changes
# to the files listed (as given in the example below):
# --- BEGIN FILE ---
   -- Diese und die folgenden Zeilen werden ignoriert --

   M    README
   M    tests/SystemTests/EXECUTE.sh
# --- END OF FILE ---


