 649                                                                     ^
 650           detected during instantiation of type "std::_Require<<error-type>>"
 651                     at line 251 of
 652                     "/sw/global/compilers/gcc/4.9.1/lib/gcc/x86_64-unknown-linu
 653                     x-gnu/4.9.1/../../../../include/c++/4.9.1/bits/alloc_traits
 654                     .h"
 655
 656 "conftest.cpp", line 33: warning: statement is unreachable
 657     return 0;
 658     ^


Reason:
=======
PGI 15.1 installed at Taurus uses internally a version of GCC which seems to be
incompatible to the one already included in PGI 15.1

Solution:
=========
Create a new file "localrc" as follows:

    makelocalrc /sw/taurus/compilers/pgi/15.1/linux86-64/15.1/bin \
           -gcc /sw/global/compilers/gcc/4.8.2/bin/gcc \
           -gpp /sw/global/compilers/gcc/4.8.2/bin/g++ \
           -g77 /sw/global/compilers/gcc/4.8.2/bin/gfortran -x -net

and copy the new file called "localrc.<HOSTNAME>" to the $HOME directory
and rename it to ".mypgcpprc":

    cp localrc.login2 ~/.mypgcpprc
    cp localrc_taurus_gcc_482 ~/.mypgcpprc

See also:
=========
 http://geco.mines.edu/guide/pgC++_man.html



