[KF, 06/18/2015]
ZIH_TAURUS2_GCC_4_9_1
svn rev 696

Error:
======
Calling

   BTS_setupsystem.sh ZIH_TAURUS_PHASE2_GCC_4_9_1 no

results in the following error:
[...]
„tests/system/PropagationFromLeftLowerCorner/Makefile.am“
SHELL SCRIPT=/home/feldhoff/opt/buildtests-4.0.0/bin/BTS_setupsystem.sh: PREPARE BUILDSYSTEM: ERROR CODE = 0
aclocal: error: aclocal: file 'config/m4/lt~obsolete.m4' does not exist

Reason:
=======
Broken links
* in config/m4:
libtool.m4 -> /usr/share/aclocal/libtool.m4
lt~obsolete.m4 -> /usr/share/aclocal/lt~obsolete.m4
ltoptions.m4 -> /usr/share/aclocal/ltoptions.m4
ltsugar.m4 -> /usr/share/aclocal/ltsugar.m4
ltversion.m4 -> /usr/share/aclocal/ltversion.m4
* in config:
ltmain.sh -> /usr/share/libtool/config/ltmain.sh
Probably, libtool, automake etc. has been run at another system.


Solution:
=========
Remove broken links und rerun script BTS_setupsystem.sh:
libtool.m4 -> /sw/global/tools/libtool/2.4.2/x86_64/share/aclocal/libtool.m4
lt~obsolete.m4 -> /sw/global/tools/libtool/2.4.2/x86_64/share/aclocal/lt~obsolete.m4
ltoptions.m4 -> /sw/global/tools/libtool/2.4.2/x86_64/share/aclocal/ltoptions.m4
ltsugar.m4 -> /sw/global/tools/libtool/2.4.2/x86_64/share/aclocal/ltsugar.m4
ltversion.m4 -> /sw/global/tools/libtool/2.4.2/x86_64/share/aclocal/ltversion.m4


