################################################################################
[KF, 2015-09-24]
scafes/trunk

Error:
======
make ends up with error message:
No Makefile available in tests/unit

Reason:
=======
* All files Makefile.am within trunk are built for development mode.
   Makefile_to_develop.am --> Makefile.am etc.
* configure had benn called with distribution mode enabled:
   configure --enable-dist=yes

Solution:
=========
* Ensure that type of Makefile.am (distribute, develop) are consistent to
  configure call (./configure --enable-dist=<no/yes>).
  * Build in development mode:
     ./BTS_scripts/BTS_preparebuildsystem.sh no
     ./bootstrap.sh
     ./configure --enable-dist=no ...
  * Build in distribution mode:
     ./BTS_scripts/BTS_preparebuildsystem.sh yes
     ./bootstrap.sh
     ./configure --enable-dist=yes ...



