Problem:
========
make[3]: Entering directory `/lustre/scratch2/zihforschung/jenkins3/workspace/ScaFES/SCAFES_ZIH_TAURUS_HASWELL_COMPILETESTS/CONFIG/ZIH_TAURUS_HASWELL_GCC_5_3_0/label/ZIH-Taurus-ScaFES/software_trunk/build/examples/HeatEqnFDM'
  CXX      HeatEqnFDM-main.o
In file included from ../.././../src/ScaFES.hpp:409:0,
                 from ../.././../examples/HeatEqnFDM/main.cpp:7:
../.././../src/ScaFES_Problem.hpp:59:40: fatal error: boost/serialization/pfto.hpp: No such file or directory
compilation terminated.
make[3]: *** [HeatEqnFDM-main.o] Error 1

Remark: No error with Boost 1.57.0.

Reason:
=======
boost/serialization/ptfo.hpp is not included anymore in boost_rootdir/include
beginning from version 1.59.0

https://mailman.cc.gatech.edu/pipermail/mlpack/2015-September/000694.html
http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_58_0/boost/serialization/pfto.hpp
http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_59_0/boost/serialization/pfto.hpp

Solution:
=========
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6639881/how-do-you-check-your-version-of-boost

Use BOOST_VERSION from boost/version.hpp and check for Boost version.
Include header file if Boost version < 1.59.0

